The issue is that `PopulateAssignedCourseData` iterates over `db.Courses`, but the instructor's `CourseAssignments` is null in the invalid model path. Let me look at the code again:

```csharp
private void PopulateAssignedCourseData(Instructor instructor)
{
    var allCourses = db.Courses;
    var instructorCourses = new HashSet<int>(instructor.CourseAssignments.Select(c => c.CourseID));
```

The issue is that `instructor.CourseAssignments` is null. 

In the test, the instructor object is created without initializing `CourseAssignments`, so when `PopulateAssignedCourseData` tries to call `Select()` on it, LINQ throws an `ArgumentNullException` because the source collection is null.

I need to initialize `CourseAssignments` to an empty list when setting up the test instructor.

